  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Apricot-Carrot Salad W/grapefruit Mint</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Salad</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Lime juice</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Red wine vinegar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Ground cumin</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Sugar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Salt &amp; white pepper to taste</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/3</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Peanut oil</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Grated ginger</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Cloves (small) garlic; minced</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Grapefruit mint; chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>pound</unit></amt>
        <item>Carrots</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Dried apricots; slivered</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit>large</unit></amt>
        <item>Romaine lettuce leaves</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Make the dressing: In a small mixing bowl add 2 tablespoons lime juice to
  red wine vinegar. Add ground cumin, sugar, salt and white pepper to taste.
  With a whisk, stir in the peanut oil to form an emulsion, then blend in
  ginger, garlic and mint. Allow the mixture to sit for one-half hour before
  using for the flavors to blend.
  
  Peel carrots, then shred with a grater or the appropriate attachment in a
  food processor. Place carrots in a large mixing bowl and add apricots. Add
  dressing, tossing salad until well coated. Spon salad onto large chilled
  romaine lettuce leaves, and serve.
  
  Source:  Shepherd's Garden Seeds pamphlet.
  
